President Obama participated in a video conference with Afghan President Ashraf Ghani and Chief Executive Officer Dr. Abdullah. They discussed the progress made since their meeting in March, including efforts to curb corruption, revive the economy, and improve regional economic connectivity. President Obama praised the performance of the Afghan security forces during the current fighting season. They also discussed ways to strengthen the Afghan National Security and Defense Forces, deepen the U.S.-Afghanistan partnership, and encourage regional cooperation to counter terrorist threats. President Obama offered continued U.S. support for the Afghan-led peace process and commended President Ghani's efforts to advance reconciliation. They committed to continuing close consultations in the future.